  "text": "TLS configuration flows through two main paths:\n\n**Definition**: `config/config.go` in prometheus/prometheus defines `ScrapeConfig`, `RemoteWriteConfig`, and `RemoteReadConfig`, all embedding `config.HTTPClientConfig` from prometheus/common. The `HTTPClientConfig` struct contains a `TLSConfig` field.\n\n**Scrape path**: `scrape/scrape.go` calls `newScrapeClient()` (line 2260), which delegates to `config_util.NewClientFromConfig()` from prometheus/common's `config/http_config.go`. That function calls `NewRoundTripperFromConfig()`, which calls `NewTLSConfig()` to build a `*tls.Config`, then optionally wraps the transport in a `TLSRoundTripper` for CA file hot-reloading.\n\n**Remote-write path**: `storage/remote/write.go` builds a `ClientConfig` from `RemoteWriteConfig.HTTPClientConfig` and passes it to `NewWriteClient()` in `storage/remote/client.go` (line 183), which again calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig()` flowing into the same prometheus/common TLS chain.\n\n**Remote-read path**: `storage/remote/storage.go` similarly builds a `ClientConfig` and calls `NewReadClient()` (line 151 of client.go), using the same `NewClientFromConfig()` pipeline.\n\n**Validation**: `cmd/promtool/main.go` has `checkTLSConfig()` (line 790) for additional file-existence validation. The core TLS validation (cert/key pairing, CA loading) lives in prometheus/common's `NewTLSConfig()` and `TLSConfig.Validate()`.\n\n**prometheus/common `config/http_config.go`** is the central file defining `TLSConfig` struct, `NewTLSConfig()` (builds `*tls.Config`), `NewClientFromConfig()`, `NewRoundTripperFromConfig()`, and `NewTLSRoundTripper()` (handles certificate hot-reloading).",
